data.text:
I haven’t published any writing this week on Medium. I had an idea for a character with many interesting stories plus advice on how to survive the end of the world. I am unsure how to publish this character and his stories best, so I haven’t yet. I wish I had done some more writing, but I didn’t have any topics speaking to me. I can’t sit down and write about just anything. I have to feel passionate about an issue to write. I thought about doing weekly prompts next week to get some much-needed writing time. My goal next week is to finish writing my new character’s stories and to publish two articles on Medium, one as a weekly prompt and another on a topic of my choosing.

Peloton, Sushi and More!

This week flew by as I was busy with work and after-school activities while also trying to stay healthy and sane. I had to cram in my Peloton Power Zone training at the end of the week, and after a 75-minute bike ride this morning, my legs are tired. The Power Zone training is a minimum of three workouts a week, and each workout is a minimum of 60 minutes. The vegetarian/pescetarian diet is going well.
